1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:06,100
Architecture Governance Copilot is our Accelerate 3.0
proof of concept from Two Tokens One Brain.

2
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:11,700
It turns architecture review discussion into
an accountable, evidence-backed record.

3
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:17,300
Product Owners and development teams prepare
the Solution Intent using the required template.

4
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:22,400
The official SI remains in Confluence,
with an ADO governance ticket for review tracking.

5
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:28,000
A Domain Architect reviews it through Teams meetings
and revision rounds until formal approval.

6
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:33,000
Here, synthetic Confluence content
is normalized into Markdown,

7
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:37,800
while synthetic text represents a Teams review transcript
produced only when transcription is enabled.

8
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:41,800
That process creates repeated administration.

9
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:47,300
Decisions, findings, risks, and actions can be spread
across the SI, meeting discussion, notes, and ADO.

10
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:52,900
Teams manually rebuild the governance record
and tracked work,

11
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:57,800
increasing the risk that evidence, ownership,
or requested changes are missed or inconsistent.

12
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:02,300
The Copilot structures both normalized inputs,
preserves evidence,

13
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:06,700
and pauses for human review before producing
a standardized record and mock ADO actions.

14
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,700
It never approves automatically.

15
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:14,800
The application begins with clear synthetic-data
and human-accountability notices.

16
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:20,800
I load the bundled review package: version 1.2
of a fictional Digital Payment Notification Service SI,

17
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:24,500
review metadata, and a timestamped transcript.

18
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:30,000
Analyze Review validates both sources
and opens a separate Human Review page.

19
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:33,700
The outcome is Changes Requested.

20
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:40,300
The summary shows one decision, three findings,
one risk, two actions, one open question,

21
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:43,600
and two missing-information items.

22
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:48,200
The decision accepts managed PostgreSQL
as the system of record.

23
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:54,600
Findings identify missing traffic-failover behaviour,
missing RTO and RPO values,

24
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:59,100
and undefined production support ownership.

25
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:02,500
Database sizing is a release risk.

26
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:07,600
Every item retains a source quote
from the SI, the transcript, or both.

27
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:11,200
This is a proposal, not an approval.

28
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:16,800
The reviewer can inspect evidence, edit fields,
and include or exclude items.

29
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:22,500
I change the first action owner
to the clearly synthetic value Taylor Kim,

30
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:27,300
then exclude the unresolved Redis question.
Evidence stays read-only.

31
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:32,400
Only now do I confirm the reviewed record
and generate outputs.

32
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:38,000
The application preserves those choices:
Taylor Kim appears in the review record

33
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:43,200
and first mock work item,
while the Redis question is absent.

34
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:48,800
Two mock Azure DevOps actions are prepared,

35
00:02:48,900 --> 00:03:04,700
and the screen confirms that
no real work item was created.

36
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:09,700
This workflow reduces manual review administration
and supports more consistent records.

37
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:14,500
It helps reduce the risk of missed findings and actions,
and improves evidence traceability.

38
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:18,500
Structured outputs can support future integration,

39
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:22,200
but every record is reviewed before generation,

40
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:26,800
and formal decision authority remains
with the Domain Architect.

41
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:32,100
The extractor interface uses a deterministic
demo implementation for reliable offline use.

42
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:35,800
It does not analyze arbitrary documents
or use a production enterprise LLM.

43
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:39,500
A future approved provider could connect
Confluence, Teams, and Azure DevOps;

44
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:42,800
none exists today.

45
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:47,000
Architecture Governance Copilot shows one practical,
human-controlled path from architecture discussion

46
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:49,700
to accountable action.
Two Tokens One Brain.
